snippet.textDisplay: As a rugby player, The thing that gets me wound up the most about football is the lack of committing to tackles and trying to get past a defender. Putting ur shoulder into there stomach lift there legs dump them on the ground and push ur shoulder into then and i know they got pads but still i'd rather make a perfect tackle then attempt to hurt someone and fail. and also if someone is going to run out, just tackle them out. I'm not gonna let someone just run out so they dont get tackle. And also if a guy is ahead of you, running for the td dive and wrap ur arms around their legs. Now the attacking which is my favourite part of rubgy, I always see players run out and ik it's strategy but just fucking bump them off and run straight at the guy like you've got pads ya know, ik you dont want to fumble but just work on not dropping the ball coz that is one of the basics of the game but i still like the sport and those are things i think football players should work on more, using the shoulder not ur head and using ur arms around their legs to take them down and commiting to getting to the end zone instead of playing it safe bump players off it makes the best highlights 😁
